      "end": 1.64,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 2.56,
      "end": 5.14,
      "text": "All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 6.08,
      "end": 11.18,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 11.84,
      "end": 15.8,
      "text": "Recorded by Christine Doer, the known as Assah, Florida.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 17.56,
      "end": 20.7,
      "text": "A subspapils, the lark and the farmer.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 21.88,
      "end": 27.6,
      "text": "A lark nested in a field of corn and was rearing her brood under cover of the ripening grain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 28.32,
      "end": 33.5,
      "text": "One day, before the young were fully fledged, the farmer came to look at the crop,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 34.12,
      "end": 41.56,
      "text": "and finding it yellowing fast, he said, I must send round word to my neighbors to come and help me reap this field.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 42.6,
      "end": 50.72,
      "text": "One of the young larks overheard him and was very much frightened, and asked her mother whether they hadn't better move house at once.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 51.86,
      "end": 53.72,
      "text": "There's no hurry replied she.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 54.26,
      "end": 58.22,
      "text": "A man who looks to his friends for help will take his time about a thing.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 59.36,
      "end": 66.92,
      "text": "In a few days, the farmer came by again and saw that the grain was overripe and falling out of the ears upon the ground.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 67.74,
      "end": 70.08,
      "text": "I must put it off no longer, he said.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 70.8,
      "end": 74.04,
      "text": "This very day I'll hire the men and set them to work at once.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 74.96,
      "end": 80.74,
      "text": "The lark heard him and said to her young, come my children, we must be off.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 81.42,
      "end": 86.2,
      "text": "He talks no more of his friends now, but is going to take things in hand himself.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 87.54,
      "end": 90.14,
      "text": "Self-help is the best help.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 91.34,
      "end": 93.76,
      "text": "End of the lark and the farmer.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
